From: Jan Chaloupka <jchaloup@redhat.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2015 15:03:19 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] more detailed explanation for update-minimum with --advisory
 option in yum-security manpage

---
 yum-utils/man8/yum-security.8 | 14 +++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/yum-utils/man8/yum-security.8 b/yum-utils/man8/yum-security.8
index 295a046..339c179 100644
--- a/yum-utils/man8/yum-security.8
+++ b/yum-utils/man8/yum-security.8
@@ -12,9 +12,9 @@ added yum \fIcommand\fPs are:
 .br 
 .I \fR yum update-minimal
 .PP 
-This works like the update command, but if you have the the package foo-1
-installed and have foo-2 and foo-3 available with updateinfo.xml then
-update-minimal will update you to foo-3.
+This works like the update command, but if you have the package foo-1 installed
+and have foo-2 (bugfix) and foo-3 (enhancement) available with updateinfo.xml
+then update-minimal --bugfix will update you to foo-2.
 .br 
 .I \fR yum updateinfo info
 .br 
@@ -139,6 +139,14 @@ security errata package) use:
 .IP
 yum --security update-minimal
 .PP
+To install the minimal update necessary to satisfy the advisory FEDORA-2707-7654 use:
+.IP
+yum update-minimal --advisory FEDORA-2707-7654
+.PP
+To update all the packages listed in the advisory FEDORA-2707-7654 to their latest versions use:
+.IP
+yum update --advisory FEDORA-2707-7654
+.PP
 To get a list of all BZs that are fixed for packages you have installed use:
 .IP
 yum updateinfo list bugzillas
